summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from the Kent Lumber Company, a corporation, to The City of Seattle of certain lands in Sections Twelve (12) and Thirteen (13), Township Twenty-two (22) North, Range Seven (7) East, W. M.; certain lands in Sections Four (4), Six (6), Seven (7) and Eight (8), Township Twenty-two (22) North Range Eight (8) East, W. M. subject to certain reservations, and appropriating the sum of Seventy-three Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($73,500) from General Fund in payment for said lands, and providing for the reimbursement of the General Fund in said sum.
